author: Chanel Kinniburgh
title: Southern Cross Station stabbing in Melbourne: Teens on the run
text:
POLICE are searching for three teenage girls following a stabbing at Southern Cross station in Melbourne’s CBD. 
Emergency services were called to the toilets at the railway station on Spencer St at about 10.20pm on Saturday night.
One of three teens involved in a stabbing. Source: Supplied 
The incident occurred at Southern Cross station. Source: Supplied 
The 21-year-old victim was slashed across her upper arm and was taken to hospital with non-life threatening injuries.
The three females involved in the altercation have been described as Islander or Asian in appearance.
WHITE NIGHT MAYHEM AS YOUTHS FACE OFF 
They fled the scene and were last seen running down Spencer St towards Flinders St.
Investigators have released images of two of the females who may be able to assist with their inquiries.
Anyone with information or who witnessed the incident is urged to contact Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000.
Originally published as Teens ‘slash woman’ at train station
